Docker Volume
==============
Basically if we run image everytime it will create new container so ,we will loose our previous container data ,so if want mantain same data for all containers wee need to use volumes.



run image with volume
-----------------------------

docker run -d -v <name of the volume>:/app -e SERVER_PORT=9090 -p 8080:9090 <name of the imgae>:<version>

if we want create 2 containers stop first one and run again same above command.


See the volumes
---------------
docker volume ls

Remove Docker Volume
-------------------
docker volume rm <name of the volume>


Docker Compose
==============
Docker compose allows us to define and run multi-container docker applications using a yml file.

docker-compose.yml
-------------------
version: "1.0"
services:
    app:
      build: .
      container_name: backend-assignment
      environment:
        SERVER_PORT: 8080
      ports:
        - 8081:8080
      depends_on:
        - postgres
      networks:
        - backend-assignment-network

    postgres:
      image: postgres:16
      container_name: postgres
      environment:
        POSTGRES_USER: manoj
        POSTGRES_PASSWORD: manoj@123
        POSTGRES_DB: backend_assignment
      ports:
        - 5433:5432
      networks:
       - backend-assignment-network
      volumes:
      - backend-assignment-data:/var/lib/postgresql/data

networks:
  backend-assignment-network:
    driver: bridge

volumes:
  backend-assignment-data:



  application.yml
  ---------------

server:
  port: ${SERVER_PORT:8080}
spring:
  application:
    name: Backend-Assignment
  datasource:
    url: jdbc:postgresql://postgres:5432/backend_assignment
    username: manoj
    password: manoj@123

  jpa:
    hibernate:
      ddl-auto: update


  to run this compose yml file we have to run below command
-------------------------------------------------------------

docker compose up --build

  to stop this compose yml file we have to run below command
-------------------------------------------------------------

docker compose down -v

